This was surprisingly delicious. I kept the ingredients the same, but changed the method a bit - I sauteed the onion, THEN added the barley, let it brown a bit, and then the mushrooms (I figured the water from the mushrooms would prevent the barley from browning). Also, because I needed my oven at a lower temp for braising, I just cooked the dish stove top. It was really yummy. I added a bit of herbes de provence, but considering how simple this was, I give it four forks for the nutrition:taste:effort ratio. :)

